=== Comic book ===
* ''Bubblegum Crisis: Grand Mal'' produced by [[Adam Warren]] via [[Dark Horse Comics]].&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|author=trebor &amp;nbsp; View profile &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;More options |url=http://groups.google.com/group/alt.fan.bgcrisis/msg/410d605a4d858007?q=group:alt.fan.bgcrisis+author:trebor%40animeigo.com&amp;hl=en&amp;lr=&amp;safe=off&amp;as_drrb=b&amp;as_mind=27&amp;as_minm=6&amp;as_miny=2000&amp;as_maxd=29&amp;as_maxm=6&amp;as_maxy=2000&amp;rnum=1&amp;ic=1 |title=Mason Largo Theory Part 2 [WAS Re: [INFO&amp;#93; ANOTHER BUBBLEGUMCRISIS FAQ (Part 3/3)&amp;#93; - alt.fan.bgcrisis &amp;#124; Google Groups |publisher=Groups.google.com |date=2000-06-28 |accessdate=2009-05-15}}&lt;/ref&gt;

===Live-action movie===
In May 2009 it was announced that a [[live-action]] movie of &quot;Bubblegum Crisis&quot; was in the early stages of production. A production agreement was signed at the 2009 [[Cannes Film Festival]].&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url=http://www.channelnewsasia.com/stories/entertainment/view/429391/1/.html |title=channelnewsasia.com |publisher=channelnewsasia.com |date=2008-11-13 |accessdate=2009-05-15}}&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2008-11-24/aic-agrees-to-live-action-bubblegum-crisis-proposal |title=AIC Agrees to Live-Action Bubblegum Crisis Proposal (Updated) |publisher=Anime News Network |date=2009-05-11 |accessdate=2009-05-15}}&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2008-11-25/pre-production-bubblegum-crisis-film-remake-image-posted |title=Pre-Production Bubblegum Crisis Film Image Posted |publisher=Anime News Network |date=2009-05-11 |accessdate=2009-05-15}}&lt;/ref&gt; The film is expected to be released late 2012 and is consulting the original anime's staff members [[Shinji Aramaki]] and [[Kenichi Sonoda]] to help tie the film with the original anime.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2009-05-14/2012-bubblegum-crisis-film-planned-with-caucasisan/asian-cast|title=2012 Bubblegum Crisis Film Planned with Caucasian/Asian Cast (Updated)|date=2009-05-14|publisher=Anime News Network|work=News|accessdate=2009-07-05}}&lt;/ref&gt;

