====Demutualised====
Ten building societies of the United Kingdom [[Demutualization|demutualised]] between 1989 and 2000, either becoming a bank or being acquired by a larger bank.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.bsa.org.uk/consumer/factsheets/100010.htm Building Society Takeovers and Flotations] Building Societies Association website . Retrieved 5 April 2007.&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref name=&quot;pollock&quot;&gt;{{Cite news
|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/business/7641925.stm
|title=Not such a good idea after all?
|work=[[bbc.co.uk]]
|publisher=BBC News
|author=Pollock, Ian
|date=2008-09-29
|accessdate=2008-10-01}}&lt;/ref&gt; By 2008, every building society that floated on the stock market in the wave of demutualisations of the 1980s and 1990s had either been sold to a conventional bank, or been [[Nationalization|nationalised]].&lt;ref name=&quot;pollock&quot; /&gt;

